It was well after midnight and I was still sitting inside my detective's office finishing the evening off at my desk with a glass of good bourbon when I was surprised to see the town mayor walk in. He was here incognito, wearing a large black coat and a fedora, having come alone.

I immediately knew something had happened for him to be here at this late hour. It was rare for a city official to seek my private detective services even in broad daylight. But it was worse than I feared. Someone had stolen the keys to the city - with the suspect still at large.
